        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 5:42AM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 542 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
West Farmington, or 9 miles northwest of Warren, moving northeast at
45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Akron, Warren, Ravenna, Cuyahoga Falls, Kent, Solon, Hudson, Niles,
Twinsburg, Tallmadge, Streetsboro, Macedonia, Cortland, Newton Falls,
Mogadore, Lordstown, Middlefield, Garrettsville, Kinsman, and North
Bloomfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
